cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.PL, cs.SY, cs.AR 

This paper is primarily focused on the security aspect of programming, specifically on the constant-time programming discipline to prevent timing side-channel attacks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the challenges of writing CT code and the need for binary-level analysis, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.PL (Programming Languages). The technique proposed in the paper is based on symbolic execution, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper also discusses the preservation of CT by compilers, which could potentially fall under cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
